# Graphics Lab Performance Monitoring System

## ?? Project Summary

A comprehensive, production-ready **CPU Performance Monitoring System** has been successfully implemented for the Graphics Lab C# Windows Forms application. The system automatically measures and displays performance metrics (CPU usage, execution time, memory allocation) for all 17 drawing algorithms, comparing performance between **slow-motion animated mode** and **direct instant rendering mode**.

---

## ?? What's New

### Core Monitoring System
- **PerformanceMonitor.cs** - Static utility class for measurement and analysis
- **PerformanceSnapshot.cs** - Data class encapsulating individual measurements
- **Form1.cs** - Enhanced with monitoring initialization and integration
- **Performance Display Label** - Visual metrics display on right side of window

### Integration Status
? **17/17 algorithms integrated** with automatic performance tracking:
- Lab 1: Single Pixel, Square Outline, Three Lines, Filled Square
- Lab 2: Line Slopes (Shallow/Steep), Gradients, RGB Gradient Bar
- Lab 3: DDA Triangle, Bresenham Line, Complex Shape, DDA Line
- Lab 4: Midpoint Circle, Polar Circle, Composite Shape, Standard Circle
- Lab 5: Shapes (multiple triangles)

### Key Features
? **Non-invasive** - Simply wraps algorithm execution (2 lines per algorithm)
? **Automatic** - Detects slow/fast mode, collects metrics, updates display
? **Thread-safe** - Uses Stopwatch precision timing and Invoke() for UI safety
? **Comprehensive** - Tracks time, CPU, memory, and mode comparisons
? **User-friendly** - Displays metrics in readable format, copyable to clipboard

