## ?? Key Metrics Explained

### Execution Time (ms)
- **What**: Total elapsed time from start to end of algorithm
- **Includes**: Algorithm logic + Thread.Sleep() (if slow mode) + screen refreshes
- **Precision**: Microseconds via `Stopwatch.GetTimestamp()`
- **Why Slow > Fast**: SLOW has intentional delays for visualization

### CPU Percentage (%)
- **What**: System-wide CPU usage during algorithm execution
- **Source**: Windows Performance Counter
- **Why Slow > Fast**: More screen refreshes = more CPU work

### Memory (MB)
- **What**: Net memory allocated/deallocated during execution
- **Method**: GC.GetTotalMemory() at start and end
- **Note**: Only captures differential; doesn't show peak usage

### Ratio (Slow/Fast)
- **Formula**: Average SLOW time / Average FAST time
- **Example**: 14.31x = Slow mode takes 14 times longer
- **Educational Value**: Quantifies animation overhead

### CPU Delta (?)
- **Formula**: Average SLOW CPU% - Average FAST CPU%
- **Interpretation**: How much more CPU animation costs
- **Example**: +9.9% = Animation adds 10% CPU overhead

